<HEADLINE>
<P>
SPOTLIGHT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
It was not the best of seasons for either Jamie Grossman or Pierce College, but 
both gained a measure of redemption in last week's 38-35 loss to Bakersfield, 
the top-ranked junior college team in the nation. 
</P>
<P>
Behind Grossman, Pierce gave Bakersfield a shock, even if it did not pull off a 
shocking upset. 
</P>
<P>
No one else had played undefeated Bakersfield closer than 12 points, but 
Grossman put Pierce on top with two early touchdown passes, then twice led the 
Brahmas (4-6) back from second-half deficits. 
</P>
<P>
Grossman, a sophomore from Cleveland High, twice completed six passes in a row. 
He finished 19 for 31 for 295 yards with three touchdowns and no interceptions. 
</P>
<P>
Jamie Grossman: Pierce 
</P>
<P>
Football: Quarterback 
</P>
<P>
Soph: 6-2, 195 pounds 
</P>
</TEXT>
