VENTURA COUNTY NEWS ROUNDUP: SIMI VALLEY; 
</P>
<P>
GROUPS TO GIVE 350 TURKEYS TO NEEDY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Southern California Water Co., working with three service groups, will present 
charities in the area with 350 turkeys to be distributed to needy families 
today. 
</P>
<P>
The water company asked Assemblywoman Cathie Wright (R-Simi Valley) to help 
coordinate disbursement of the turkeys in the second annual "Operation Gobble." 
</P>
<P>
Working with Simi Valley Care and Share, the Knights of Columbus and the Rotary 
Club, Wright will help distribute the turkeys to the most needy people in the 
area, her aides said. 
</P>
<P>
In other holiday action, the Ventura Jaycees announced that the group will bake 
300 dozen cookies to send to the 1,800 Port Hueneme-based Seabees deployed in 
Saudi Arabia. 
</P>
<P>
Calling the project "A little home for the holidays," the Jaycees are scheduled 
to bake and package the cookies at Pizza Hut on Main Street all day Saturday, 
Dec. 1. The Jaycees are seeking $10 donations, for which the donor's name and 
address will be included on a dozen cookies shipped to the troops overseas. 
</P>
