<P>
VENTURA COUNTY NEWS ROUNDUP: COUNTYWIDE; 
</P>
<P>
SECRETARY TO SCHAEFER QUITS OVER FIRING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By DARYL KELLEY 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
County Supervisor Madge L. Schaefer's secretary resigned Wednesday, saying she 
could no longer work for the lame-duck supervisor. 
</P>
<P>
Carol Claassen said her decision was based, in part, on the supervisor's 
dismissal of another staff member Monday. 
</P>
<P>
Schaefer ordered aide Doug Johnson out of her Thousand Oaks office during an 
angry confrontation after she found out that he had agreed to take a job with 
her successor, Maria K. VanderKolk. 
</P>
<P>
Claassen said she turned in her resignation Wednesday partly "because I was 
very upset about the way Madge treated Doug. It was terrible. He is the most 
loyal, professional individual I have ever known, and she told him he didn't 
know anything about loyalty." 
</P>
<P>
Claassen said she was also upset about Schaefer's assertions to reporters 
Tuesday that she had not fired Johnson but only placed him on leave. According 
to the secretary, Schaefer had directed another staff member to draw up 
Johnson's termination papers after the confrontation, then changed her mind 
when she found out that Johnson was entitled to 60 days severance pay. 
</P>
<P>
Schaefer refused to comment on Claassen's resignation. The supervisor said 
previously that she dismissed Johnson because he had not told her about his job 
plans, which she learned of through an anonymous letter last weekend. DARYL 
KELLEY 
</P>
</TEXT>
