<HEADLINE>
<P>
2 PEOPLE KILLED IN SEPARATE CRASHES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Two people were killed in car accidents within one hour of each other Wednesday 
night near Oxnard as highways across the Southland filled with holiday traffic, 
officials said. 
</P>
<P>
One person was killed on Victoria Avenue north of Gonzales Road about 6:30 
p.m., a spokesman for the California Highway Patrol said. In a separate 
accident, a person died on Pacific Coast Highway south of Channel Islands 
Boulevard about 7:30 p.m., the CHP said. 
</P>
<P>
No further information was available about the accidents or the victims' 
identities, he said. 
</P>
<P>
The Ventura County coroner's office would not respond to calls Wednesday night. 
</P>
</TEXT>
