DETECTIVE SAYS WORTHY CONTACTED PORTLAND ESCORT SERVICE LAST SEASON 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MARK HEISLER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
James Worthy contacted an escort service on a Laker trip to Portland last 
season, a Portland detective said Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
Det. David Simpson said Worthy called Allstar Models and Escorts last Feb. 6, 
requesting an escort. 
</P>
<P>
The escort service was under investigation at the time. 
</P>
<P>
Simpson said that the caller left a phone number, corresponding to that of the 
Marriott Hotel where the team was staying, and a room number corresponding to 
the one in which Worthy was registered. 
</P>
<P>
Simpson said no action was taken against Worthy. 
</P>
<P>
"There wasn't any reason to," Simpson said from Portland. "We had our case made 
already." 
</P>
<P>
Valerie Walton, proprietress of the company, has been found guilty on six 
counts of promoting prostitution, a felony in Oregon. She has not yet been 
sentenced. Her sister, Marla, an employee, pleaded guilty to one count and was 
put on probation. 
</P>
<P>
Worthy was arrested last week in Houston on a charge of soliciting prostitution 
from an escort company. He pleaded not guilty at his arraignment in Houston 
Tuesday. MARK HEISLER 
</P>
