<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN GABRIEL VALLEY DIGEST: ALTADENA; 
</P>
<P>
ZONING RULING DELAYED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A zoning variance that has become the center of a controversy over alleged 
bootleg rentals in this unincorporated area was delayed Monday by the county 
Regional Planning Commission. 
</P>
<P>
The commission made no decision on the variance requested by homeowners 
Margaret and Guillermo Villareal. 
</P>
<P>
It is opposed by the Altadena Town Council. Instead, the commission asked its 
staff to survey residents surrounding the Villareals' home in the 1500 block of 
East Woodbury Drive. 
</P>
<P>
The neighborhood is zoned for one house per 7,500 square feet. But a county 
building and safety official told commission members Monday that 38 nearby 
residences have two buildings per lot and another 19 have three buildings per 
lot. The survey could take at least three months, county planners said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
