<HEADLINE>
<P>
10 AREA TEAMS ADVANCE IN FOOTBALL PLAYOFFS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Paramount, Lynwood and Downey, three San Gabriel Valley League teams, have 
advanced to the second round of the Southern Section Division II high school 
football playoffs Friday night. 
</P>
<P>
They are among 10 Long Beach/Southeast area teams still alive. 
</P>
<P>
Top-seeded and undefeated (11-0) Paramount, which defeated Rio Mesa, 27-7, last 
week, will play host to Muir (8-3). 
</P>
<P>
Lynwood (6-5), a 31-27 winner over Thousand Oaks, will be at home against 10-1 
El Toro, and Downey (8-3), which beat Royal, 17-10, will host Mission Viejo 
(10-1). 
</P>
<P>
In Division III, St. Paul (6-3-2) will play 6-5 Beverly Hills at El Segundo 
High School. The Swordsmen advanced with a 21-8 victory over Orange. 
</P>
<P>
In Division IV, Bell Gardens (8-3) will have a home game against 11-0 Santa 
Margarita. The Lancers defeated Walnut, 3-0, last week. 
</P>
<P>
In Division VII, Glenn (8-2), a 40-19 winner over St. Francis, will play at 
10-1 Lompoc, and 9-2 La Mirada, which defeated Harvard, 21-14, will play host 
to top-seeded 9-0 Serra. 
</P>
<P>
In Division IX, Whittier Christian (10-0), which downed San Jacinto, 52-6, will 
play at Desert (8-3), and 5-5 Valley Christian, which advanced by beating 
Carpinteria, 17-14, will host 8-3 Bishop. 
</P>
<P>
And in Division X, Leffingwell Christian, which had a bye last week, will play 
Camp Kilpatrick (6-3-1) at Excelsior High School. 
</P>
<P>
All games start at 7:30. 
</P>
