<P>
PETER A. PENDER; ONE OF WORLD'S BEST BRIDGE PLAYERS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Peter A. Pender, 54, considered one of the world's leading bridge players. 
</P>
<P>
Pender, of San Francisco, and his partner, Hugh Ross of Oakland, were members 
of a California foursome that won several national titles and one world 
championship (the 1985 Bermuda Bowl in Brazil) in the last several years. Last 
year the team finished second to Brazil in the Bermuda Bowl competition in 
Australia. In 1966 Pender was judged the best overall bridge player in the 
nation and was awarded the McKenney Trophy. In San Francisco on Sunday of the 
complications of AIDS. 
</P>
