<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFLY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Van Nuys Firm Loses Big Award: A jury that ordered General Electric Co. to pay 
$70.8 million to a tiny Van Nuys firm was overruled by a Superior Court judge, 
who slashed the award to $9.8 million. The firm, American Aviation Industries, 
is now effectively in the hole because the jury in July also had ordered AAI to 
repay GE about $14 million, and that part of the case was upheld by Judge 
Stephen D. Petersen, said Bert Cooper, a lawyer for GE. The companies sued each 
other over a failed venture in which they planned to retrofit Lockheed 
corporate jets with GE-made engines. 
</P>
