<HEADLINE>
<P>
PRO FOOTBALL REPORT / WEEKDAY UPDATE; 
</P>
<P>
AROUND THE NFL; 
</P>
<P>
CARDINALS CLAIM MANLEY OFF WAIVERS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Dexter Manley, two days after his reinstatement following a one-year ban from 
the NFL for substance abuse, was claimed off waivers by the Phoenix Cardinals. 
</P>
<P>
Manley, 31, is not eligible to play in a game until Dec. 9. 
</P>
<P>
The Rams (3-7) put in a claim, but the Cardinals (2-8) had priority. 
</P>
<P>
Today's Thanksgiving Day NFL menu has the Denver Broncos playing at Detroit at 
9:30 a.m., PST, and the Washington Redskins playing at Dallas at 1 p.m. 
</P>
<P>
The Redskins (6-4) are the only team with realistic playoff hopes. 
</P>
</TEXT>
