<TEXT>
<P>
The Seattle SuperSonics suspended guard Dale Ellis without pay for five days 
for disciplinary reasons. KIRO-TV reported that Ellis and Sonic forward Xavier 
McDaniel had a fistfight at the SuperSonics' office Wednesday, but McDaniel 
denied that. Ellis, not eligible to come off the injured list until a Nov. 29 
game, could not be reached for comment. 
</P>
