<HEADLINE>
<P>
COLLEGE FOOTBALL REPORT / WEEKDAY UPDATE; 
</P>
<P>
USC; 
</P>
<P>
THIRD TIGHT END OUT WITH INJURY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JERRY CROWE 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
USC is down to its fourth tight end, sophomore Bob Crane, after redshirt 
freshman Brad Banta suffered a stress fracture in his left leg Saturday in the 
Trojans' 45-42 victory over UCLA. 
</P>
<P>
Earlier this season, starter Frank Griffin suffered a season-ending knee 
injury, and backup Yonnie Jackson a season-ending foot injury. 
</P>
<P>
Banta was injured when a Bruin defensive back fell on his leg, Coach Larry 
Smith said. 
</P>
<P>
Inside linebacker Matt Gee strained his right knee during last Saturday's game 
after removing a leg brace because it was uncomfortable. 
</P>
<P>
"The doctor about tore his head off," Smith said. "And we (coaches) didn't know 
he didn't have it on because they wear those (braces) below their pads." 
</P>
<P>
Redshirt freshman Gidion Murrell will start at inside linebacker in place of 
Gee. JERRY CROWE 
</P>
</TEXT>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA112290-0197 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 311964 </DOCID>
<DATE>
<P>
