<HEADLINE>
<P>
COLLEGE FOOTBALL REPORT / WEEKDAY UPDATE; 
</P>
<P>
AROUND THE NATION; 
</P>
<P>
OREGON STATE COACH WON'T BE BACK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Dave Kragthorpe won't be back next year as Oregon State's coach, it was 
announced Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
"After a lengthy and considerable discussion this morning, Coach Kragthorpe and 
I have mutually agreed to make a change at the head coaching position," Oregon 
State Athletic Director Dutch Baughman said. 
</P>
<P>
The Beavers were 1-10 in 1990 and had a record of 17-48-2 in six seasons under 
Kragthorpe. 
</P>
<P>
The University of Alabama faculty senate, citing the failure of Arizona voters 
to approve a holiday honoring Martin Luther King Jr., urged the school's 
football team not to play in the Fiesta Bowl if asked. 
</P>
<P>
The resolution was passed, 19-10, and will be forwarded to Roger Sayer, 
university president, and Pat Green, senate president. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Wire 
</P>
</TYPE>
<SUBJECT>
<P>
OREGON STATE UNIVERSITY; COACHES; FOOTBALL; RESIGNATIONS 
</P>
</SUBJECT>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA112290-0198 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 311971 </DOCID>
