<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY EARNINGS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Metalclad Corp.: The Anaheim insulation and asbestos abatement firm said it had 
net earnings of $75,828 in the third quarter, down from net earnings of 
$224,906 a year earlier. 
</P>
<P>
Revenue of $8 million for the period ended Sept. 30 was up 6.6% from $7.5 
million. For the first nine months, Metalclad posted a net loss of $73,346, 
contrasted with net income of $740,394 for the comparable period in 1989. 
Revenue, principally from insulation contracting services, asbestos abatement 
services and insulation material sales, was $20.2 million for the first nine 
months, down 11% from the year-earlier $22.7 million. 
</P>
</TEXT>
