<HEADLINE>
<P>
DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: EAGLE ROCK MAN BEATEN BY GROUP 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
An Eagle Rock man was beaten and stabbed outside his house late Saturday night 
by a group of young men, Los Angeles police said. 
</P>
<P>
Henry Raul Espino, 24, told police he was in his house in the 1600 block of 
Colorado Boulevard when he heard glass breaking about 10:40 p.m. When he went 
out to investigate, he was assaulted by about 15 men in their late teens to 
early 20s, said Detective Joe Friend. 
</P>
<P>
Espino was treated at Glendale Adventist Medical Center for cuts and bruises 
and released. 
</P>
</TEXT>
